title: Rain stops play in Taiwan's Yeangder tournament
text:
TAIPEI: Rain brought a halt to the second round of Taiwan's $500,000 Yeangder Tournament Players Championship on Friday. 

The second round will be played on Saturday instead, with the third and final round to be played Sunday, organisers said. 

Taiwan hopeful Lin Wen-tang and countryman Hung Chun-kang remain tied at the top of the leaderboard after both shot five-under-par 67 in the opening round on Thursday. Stay updated on the go with Times of India News App. Click here to download it for your device.
